Sentencas: Sr2FeCo0.2Ni0.2Mo0.6O6-6 (SFCNM) and Sr2FeNi0.4Mo0.6O6-6 (SFNM) were prepared as the hydrogen electrode materials for solid oxide cells (SOCs) and comparatively investigated by density function theory (DFT) and experiments to demonstrate the benefit of Co addition.
Titulo: An active and stable hydrogen electrode of solid oxide cells with exsolved Fe-Co-Ni nanoparticles from Sr2FeCo0.2Ni0.2Mo0.6O6-6 double-perovskite

Sentencas: The reduced SFCNM (R-SFCNM) and SFNM (R-SFNM) contain exsolved Fe-Co-Ni and Fe-Ni nanoparticles, respectively.
Titulo: An active and stable hydrogen electrode of solid oxide cells with exsolved Fe-Co-Ni nanoparticles from Sr2FeCo0.2Ni0.2Mo0.6O6-6 double-perovskite

Sentencas: DFT indicates that Fe-Co-Ni has optimized combination of the d-band center (descriptor of catalyst activity) and adsorption behavior for H2O, H2, H, and OH.
Titulo: An active and stable hydrogen electrode of solid oxide cells with exsolved Fe-Co-Ni nanoparticles from Sr2FeCo0.2Ni0.2Mo0.6O6-6 double-perovskite

Sentencas: The cell with SFCNM hydrogen electrode, La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-6 (LSGM) electrolyte, and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-6 (LSCF) oxygen electrode (Cell-SFCNM) demonstrates a higher performance than that with an SFNM hydrogen electrode (Cell-SFNM) at temperatures between 700 and 850 & DEG;C in both solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC, 3% H2O-97% H2/air) and solid oxide electrolysis cell (SOEC, 20% H2O-80% H2/air) modes.
Titulo: An active and stable hydrogen electrode of solid oxide cells with exsolved Fe-Co-Ni nanoparticles from Sr2FeCo0.2Ni0.2Mo0.6O6-6 double-perovskite

Sentencas: At 850 and 700 & DEG;C, the peak power density is 1.23 and 0.48 W & BULL;cm-2 in SOFC mode, while the current density is 1.25 and 0.37 A & BULL;cm-2 at 1.3 V in SOEC mode, respectively.
Titulo: An active and stable hydrogen electrode of solid oxide cells with exsolved Fe-Co-Ni nanoparticles from Sr2FeCo0.2Ni0.2Mo0.6O6-6 double-perovskite

Sentencas: The performance degradation rates at 750 & DEG;C are 0.17 mV & BULL;h-1 in SOFC and 0.15 mV & BULL;h-1 in SOEC modes within 150 h, which are improved by Co doping.
Titulo: An active and stable hydrogen electrode of solid oxide cells with exsolved Fe-Co-Ni nanoparticles from Sr2FeCo0.2Ni0.2Mo0.6O6-6 double-perovskite
